- The `loop()` function continuously reads data from the sensors every 5 seconds.
   - It reads temperature and humidity from the DHT22 sensor, pressure from the BMP180 sensor, and wind speed from an anemometer (connected to an analog pin).
   - The data is displayed on the LCD screen .
   - The `checkForAlerts()` function checks if the weather conditions exceed predefined thresholds and displays alerts on the LCD screen if necessary.
